#TheHousemaidMovie

THE HOUSEMAID is a wildly entertaining thriller starring Sydney Sweeney and Amanda Seyfried, based on the best-selling book. From director Paul Feig, the film plunges audiences into a twisted world where perfection is an illusion, and nothing is as it seems. Trying to escape her past, Millie (Sweeney) accepts a job as a live-in housemaid for the wealthy Nina (Seyfried) and Andrew Winchester (Brandon Sklenar). But what begins as a dream job quickly unravels into something far more dangerous ‚Äì a sexy, seductive game of secrets, scandal, and power. Behind the Winchesters‚Äô closed doors lies a world of shocking twists that will leave you guessing until the very end.

snippet.title: Fred again.. - Rooftop Live (Fede‚Äôs Roof, Naples)
snippet.description:
After a show i never quite know what to do. like you go from being filled with the most adreneline ever, to suddenly being like alone or basically alone. Often I just play songs im working on and jam on my keyboard to try ideas out to try n calm down and stuff, cos i cant really be social often. 

So when i saw fedde commenting on a post that he had a rooftop that overlooked the show i thought wow this could be like my dream afters. Just going straight up there and get to play songs on my ones and still get to see and feel the energy of the show as everyone leaves!

I played this whole set just to fedde and the beautiful nonna who also lives in this building. It was a lovely sight to look up occasionally and see them both there. Him dancing her sitting. Me a bit of both.

thankyou to Fede. 

directed by loose
shot by theo batterham & charlie hutchins
edit by charlie hutchins
recorded by tony friend
grade by tim smith
technical producer josh barnes
additional help from gianmarco
security by glen!

snippet.title: Springsteen: Deliver Me From Nowhere | Official Trailer
snippet.description:
Watch the new trailer for SPRINGSTEEN: DELIVER ME FROM NOWHERE. Starring Jeremy Allen White & Jeremy Strong. Only in theaters Oct 24.

‚ÄúSpringsteen: Deliver Me from Nowhere‚Äù chronicles the making of Bruce Springsteen‚Äôs 1982 ‚ÄúNebraska‚Äù album. Recorded on a 4-track recorder in Springsteen‚Äôs New Jersey bedroom, the album marked a pivotal time in his life and is considered one of his most enduring works‚Äîa raw, haunted acoustic record populated by lost souls searching for a reason to believe. 
 
‚Äú‚ÄòNebraska‚Äô is where Bruce chose truth over expectation‚Äîa choice that still reverberates through everything he‚Äôs written since. At that crossroads, he could have chased the bright lights and the roar of arenas, but instead he turned inward, armed only with silence, a four-track recorder, and the courage to confront himself. For him to trust me with telling that story‚Äîthe most vulnerable chapter of his life‚Äîis the greatest honor I‚Äôve ever had as a filmmaker,‚Äù says Cooper.
 
‚ÄúThis film takes a couple years out of my life and looks at them very closely, a time when I made ‚ÄòNebraska‚Äô and went through some personal difficulties,‚Äù says Springsteen. ‚ÄúI‚Äôm so appreciative of Jeremy Allen White and the entire cast for their wonderful and moving performances‚Äîand Scott Cooper, one of the most generous collaborators I‚Äôve ever worked with.‚Äù
 
Starring Jeremy Allen White as Bruce Springsteen, the film is directed by Scott Cooper from his adaptation of Warren Zanes‚Äô book of the same name. ‚ÄúSpringsteen: Deliver Me from Nowhere‚Äù also features Jeremy Strong as Springsteen‚Äôs long-time confidant and manager, Jon Landau; Paul Walter Hauser as guitar tech Mike Batlan; Odessa Young as Faye; Stephen Graham as Springsteen‚Äôs father, Doug; Gaby Hoffman as Springsteen‚Äôs mother, Adele; and David Krumholtz as Columbia executive, Al Teller. 
 
The film is produced by Cooper, Ellen Goldsmith-Vein, Eric Robinson and Scott Stuber. Tracey Landon, Jon F. Vein and Zanes executive produce. The film includes an original score by composer Jeremiah Fraites, cinematography by Masanobu Takayanagi, production design by Stefania Cella, costume design by Kasia Walicka-Maimone, and is edited by Pamela Martin.

Two Much With Kajol And Twinkle Official Trailer

Created by Banijay Asia

Kajol and Twinkle are serving up a talk show with a twist - equal parts masti, magic and maybe even some manic energy. Expect wild hot takes, controversial opinions and the kind of honesty that makes you say, ‚ÄúDude, same!‚Äù 
Joining them are their friends who just happen to be some of the biggest stars in the country (and even the world). With eight unique pairs gracing the couch this season, the conversations jump from filmy nostalgia to family drama, love, paparazzi, fame and everything in between.
What sets it apart is the unapologetic female gaze - a perspective that‚Äôs funny, sharp, and not afraid to hold up a mirror to society. One moment you‚Äôre laughing embarrassingly loudly, the next you‚Äôre caught off guard by an insight that might make you question your own life choices. 
Basically, it‚Äôs a vibe: two women side-by-side, yapping with their friends. Think of it as the fun table at the party, sunny, chatty, and just unhinged enough to keep you hooked.
